<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spaniard Sainz wins Cyprus Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- It was a one-two finish for
Ford at the Cyprus Rally on Sunday, as Spaniard Carlos Sainz and
Scot Colin McRae eased off the throttle through the six final
stages of the Rally in Limassol.
</P>
<P>
France's Peugeot rival Francois Delecour finished third and
England's Richard Burns was fourth in a Subaru.
</P>
<P>
Marcus Gronholm of Finland leads the season standings with 44
point followed by McRae (42), Burns (41), Saniz (37) and Tommi
Makinen (28).
</P>
<P>
Two-time world champion Sainz finished the rally 37.3 seconds
ahead of McRae and 1 minute 30.8 seconds faster than Delecour.
</P>
<P>
The one-two finish for Ford padded its lead on the
manufacturers' championship, with 79 points over Subaru's 64
points. Peugeot came in third place with 58 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Cyprus staged a World Championship rally.
The championship now moves to the Tour of Corsica (Sept. 29 - Oct.
1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
