<HEADLINE> SADC to Hold Health Equity Conference in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A three-day conference
on building alliances for health equity in the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) region is to take place here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Equinet, a regional network of civil society and health
sector organizations, will sponsor the event with the support of
the Canadian International Development Research Center and U. S.
Rockefeller Foundation.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Meeson, spokeswoman for South Africa's Center for Health
Policy and a member of the Equinet, said delegates from across the
SADC region and the international community are expected to attend
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The conference will cover discussions on AIDS and equity,
health and human rights, equity in termination of pregnancy
services and allocation of health resources, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
