<HEADLINE> Castro Welcomes Meets Chinese Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro
Sunday met with a Chinese Communist Party (CCP) delegation, which
concluded its visit to the island on the same day.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries and other issues of common
were discussed by Castro and the delegation members during an
interview held Sunday night at the Council of the State in Havana.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation is led by Li Tieying, a member of the
CCP political bureau and president of the Chinese Social Sciences
Academy.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by Song Defu, minister of
personnel of China, who arrived in Havana Saturday, while on the
Cuban side the meeting was attended by Vice President Carlos Lague
and Jose Ramon Balaguer, both members of the Cuban Communist Party
's Political Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived in Cuba Wednesday and from that
date it developed a working agenda that included talks with
Balaguer and with Interior Minister Ricardo Cabrisas, among others.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also toured places of economic, historical, and
social interest in the Cuban capital, and also in the neighboring
province of Matanzas. 
</P>
