<HEADLINE> U.N. Holds Coordination Mechanism Meeting on Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opening a coordination mechanism meeting of the United Nations,
the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) and the
government of Sierra Leone Monday at U.N. headquarters in New York,
Annan alerted the meeting of humanitarian implications of the
continued instability in Sierra Leone and the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
The latest number of internally displaced persons in Sierra
Leone exceeds 300,000 with another 37,000 Sierra Leonean refugees
in neighboring Liberia, he added.
</P>
<P>
An August meeting of troop-contributing countries to the U.N.
Mission Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL) highlighted the responsibility of
the entire international community to assist the U.N. to achieve a
political solution in Sierra Leone with the involvement of the
ECOWAS.
</P>
<P>
RUF rebels reignited Sierra Leone's nine-year civil war in May
by seizing about 500 U.N. peacekeepers, which severely embarrassed
the U.N. and prompted a reassessment of the U.N. peacekeeping
mission in that country.
</P>
<P>
Annan has proposed that the strength of the UNAMSIL be
increased to 20,500 from the current ceiling of 13,000. The
proposal is under the Security Council's consideration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
