<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP to Enhance Development Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at a UNDP ministerial meeting at the U.N. headquarters
in New York, Annan said the UNDP, the development arm of the world
body, can help these countries build "platforms" of education and
technology to benefit from the "express train" of globalization.
</P>
<P>
"Through the UNDP, the U.N. is present all over the world, and
is seen to be dealing with the actual problems faced by the great
majority of the world's people," he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief expressed his dissatisfaction with the UNDP's
lack of resources, describing it as "a sad state of affairs."
</P>
<P>
The meeting, themed rebuilding support for United Nations
development cooperation, is the first of its kind to examine the
UNDP in the wider context of its role in the new circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1965, the UNDP has resident officers in over 100
countries. The organization strives to reduce poverty, increase
jobs, enhance technical cooperation between industrialized and
developing nations, protect the environment and ensure women's
rights. 
</P>
