<HEADLINE> Two Die From Fireworks Factory Blast in Vilnius </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Two people have died from
severe burns received in an explosion at a fireworks firm in
Vilnius, capital of Lithuania, the Interfax news agency reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The firm's production director, Arunas Balsis, 32, died on
September 6 from burns covering nearly his entire body, and the
firm's engineer, Vidmantas Cerniauskas, 28, died Sunday from burns
over 60 percent of his body, Interfax cited the Vilnius clinic as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred on September 5 when explosive substances
caught fire in the office of the Blikas, a Vilnius pyrotechnic
firm specializing in fireworks. Fire in the premises was
extinguished before the firefighters' arrival. Nobody was killed
in the blast, but several people were injured. The building
suffered minor damage.
</P>
<P>
A criminal case has been launched and an investigation is now
being conducted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
