<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, September 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Indonesian government expected to find a
permanent solution to problems arising from the continued presence
of East Timorese refugees in East Tenggara Province, a senior
official said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Indonesia does not want to be blamed all the time for every
case emerging (due to the presence of) the refugees and the
militias," Coordinating Minister for Political, Social and
Security Affairs Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said after meeting with
President Abdurrahman Wahid at the Merdeka Palace. (Indonesia-East
Timor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tareq Aziz said Monday
that it is wrong for the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC) to make the decision to increase oil output by a
big margin.
</P>
<P>
"We think the decision is wrong and the market does not
actually need such an increase," Aziz said in a televised
interview, referring to the agreement by the OPEC oil ministerial
meeting on Sunday to increase oil production by 800,000 barrels a
day starting from October in the face of soaring prices in world
market. (Iraq-OPEC-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami
proposed on Monday to give the Palestinians "functional autonomy"
over the Temple Mount in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Israel Radio, Ben-Ami said this would give
"symbolic expression" to the Palestinians desire for sovereignty
over the area, paving the way for an agreement.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that "there can not be joint sovereignty" over
the holy site. (Israel-Palestine-Sovereignty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Sierra Leone has called for international assistance
to help solve the pressing issue of refugees being driven out from
Guinea, according to reports reaching here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone's Ambassador to Guinea Sheku Ba Saccoh was quoted
as saying in Monrovia, capital of Guinea, that the United Nations
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) should adopt some emergency
measures to address the horrifying situation in the west African
country.
</P>
<P>
Saccoh said refugees from Liberia and Sierra Leone had been
thrown out of their homes in Guinea in the middle of the rainy
season and were desperate for shelter. (SLeone-Refugee) 
</P>
