<HEADLINE> Two Dead, Five Missing in Sea Collision off Danish Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Two people drowned and five
others were reported missing in a collision Sunday between a
Polish sailboat and a freighter in the North Sea.
</P>
<P>
The collision happened about 40 kilometers off the coast of
Denmark, said Danish emergency services Monday.
</P>
<P>
Emergency sources said all eight people on the sailboat fell
into the water. Two of them drowned and only one survivor was
pulled from the water before darkness fell.
</P>
<P>
The 42-foot sailboat, a training vessel for enthusiasts to
practice their sailing skills, was reportedly traveling on a
collision course with the cargo ship, which was coming from the
opposite direction.
</P>
<P>
She was inadvertently rammed by the freighter and sank
immediately.
</P>
<P>
Rescue ships and helicopters were dispatched to the scene.
Rescue workers were continuing their search for the five missing
persons, but fear they may have drowned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
