<HEADLINE> Turkey Upbeat over Results at Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkish State Minister in
charge of sports Fikret Unlu said on Monday that he is very much
hopeful over the performance of Turkish athletes at the Olympic
games in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Unlu, prior to his departure from Ankara to Sydney, told
reporters that the biggest motivation for the athletes is that the
awards had been announced before the games, reported the Anatolia
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"The winning athletes will work as a sports consultant after
they are 30 years old," Unlu said. "They will be paid the wages of
a first-degree government worker and therefore their future is
guaranteed."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the announcement of awards to be given to Turkish
athletes had raised expectations from them in Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"We want to win more medals than we did in 1960 at Rome
Olympics," Unlu declared, referring to the fact that the Turkish
athletes won 7 gold medals in 1960.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the Turkish athletes who are
participating in the Olympics will also get morale support from
the Turkish workers living in Australia, adding that Australia,
after Germany, has the second highest number of Turks living
within its borders. Unlu expressed his conviction that Turkey
has a chance to win medals in every branch of sports which Turkish
athletes are to attend in Sydney. 
