<HEADLINE> China Steps up Production Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government today
urged Chinese enterprises to pay more attention to production
safety.
</P>
<P>
Production in Chinese enterprises is plagued with problems,
especially in private and township enterprises, according to the
results of a recent inspection organized jointly by the State
Economic and Trade Commission (SETC), the Ministry of Public
Security, the Ministry of Supervision and the All-China Federation
of Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of production safety with SETC said that
the central government will spare no efforts to close down
substandard fireworks factories, oil refineries, small mines and
video arcades.
</P>
<P>
Accident-prone sectors such as coal, electricity, oil,
petrochemical and forestry were given special attention during the
inspection, he added.
</P>
<P>
Three deadly accidents, each claiming more than ten lives, have
occurred in south China's Guangdong Province since October last
year.
</P>
<P>
Other notable examples include the June 22 air crash in central
China's Hubei Province, the June 22 Yangtze River shipwreck in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, the June 30 fireworks
explosion in Jiangmen City in south China's Guangdong Province,
and an explosion at the Dianjiang fireworks factory in Chongqing
Municipality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
