<HEADLINE> Project Launched to Boost Chinese Culture Among Overseas Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A project to boost
spreading of the general knowledge on the Chinese culture among
overseas Chinese was launched Monday in the Hong Kong Exhibition
and Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
The project will be operated both in English and traditional
Chinese characters over the Internet by two giant Hong Kong-based
portals, tom.com and china.com.
</P>
<P>
The content of the project includes the general knowledge on
China and the nation, modern Chinese language, Chinese literature,
Chinese history, geography, traditional culture, and historical
places and scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
It is to meet the demands of over 30 million overseas Chinese
in more than 100 countries to inherit the cultural traditions of
the Chinese nation. 
</P>
