<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Asian Games Bid Mascot Named "Hong Kong" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The mascot of Hong Kong's
2006 Asian Games bid has been officially named as "Hong Kong" to
reflect Hong Kong's characteristics of being full of energy and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The name was revealed by Timothy Fok, Vice Chairman of Asian
Games Bid Committee cum President of Sports Federation and Olympic
Committee of Hong Kong, during the 2006 Asian Games Bid Mascot
Naming Competition Prize Presentation Ceremony held at the Hong
Kong International Airport.
</P>
<P>
"We have received about 1,500 entries. Apart from the local
entries, some of the suggestions were sent from the Chinese
mainland and Europe," Fok said.
</P>
<P>
"Through an open competition to name the mascot, we hope to
further raise community awareness towards the Asian Games bid and
to get the public involved more in our work," he added.
</P>
<P>
The winner, Yam Chi Hung, was chosen by a panel of judges
comprising members of the Bid committee and four guest judges.
</P>
