<HEADLINE> Opposition Wins Macedonian Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The "For Macedonia Together,"
the opposition alliance in Macedonia, won a "great victory" in
Sunday's local elections by taking control of most large cities,
Branko Crvenkovski, the leader of the group, said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The group won an overwhelming number of votes in the first
round in Skopje, capital of Macedonia, as well as in Ohrid Stip,
Kocani, Veles and other major cities, Crvenkovski said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope Prime Minister Ljubco Georgievski will fulfill his
pledge and call for early parliamentary elections," he said.
</P>
<P>
Georgievski promised to hold early elections if the government
coalition of his VMRO DPMNE, the Democratic Alternative and the
Democratic Party of Albanians, lost the local vote by more than 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
Elections went smoothly in most areas, and clashes only
occurred in areas inhabited by Albanians. Eight people were
reportedly injured. 
</P>
