<HEADLINE> France: EU Decision on Austria to Be Announced Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's (EU)
decision on whether or not to lift sanctions against Austria will
be announced soon, said a French leading official on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"This should not be delayed too long. It is a question of hours
or days," said French Delegate Minister of European Affairs Pierre
Moscovici.
</P>
<P>
The three "wise men" -- former Finnish President Martti
Ahtisaari, German jurist Jochen Frowein, and former Spanish
Foreign Minister Marcelino Oreja, who were appointed by the
European Court on Human Rights to evaluate the political situation
in Austria after the entry into government by the extreme-right --
have proposed to France, the presiding EU presidency state, to
lift sanctions against Austria.
</P>
<P>
EU imposed symbolic sanctions against Austria after the extreme-
right Freedom Party led by Joerg Haider entered government in
February. The sanctions include a suspension of bilateral
cooperation between the 14 other EU countries and Austria, minimal
reception of Austrian ambassadors, and refusal to support Austrian
candidates for international posts.
</P>
<P>
Denmark has already called for a lifting of the sanctions,
while Britain expressed that it also would welcome proposals by
the three "wise men."  
</P>
</TEXT>
