<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerians Support Audit of Govt Accounts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Most Nigerians have expressed
their support to the resolution of the House of Representatives to
audit all the financial books of the three arms of government, The
Post Express newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The House of Representatives last Wednesday passed a motion
mandating the Auditor-General of the Federation to probe the
financial books of all arms of government.
</P>
<P>
The motion came after the pressure on the House to subject to
self-probe in on-going anti-corruption crusade by the government.
</P>
<P>
According to a nationwide poll conducted by the newspaper, a
three-quarter of Nigerians surveyed support the motion ordering
the auditor-general to comb through the government financial books.
</P>
<P>
Those who are in favor of auditing government accounts said it
was the only way to build public trust in the governance, adding
that such development would help bring sanity and financial
discipline to the nation's public sector.
</P>
<P>
They argued that by allowing the auditor-general to scrutinize
their accounts, the three arms of government would be sending a
positive signal to the international community of the government's
determination to wipe out the corruption in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
