<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Beats Lithuania in Olympic Tune-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic hosts Australia's
men cagers defeat medal favorite Lithuania 88-80 in a warm-up game
in Wollongong on Monday, boosting their confidence of winning
their first-ever Olympic medal in the men's basketball competition.
</P>
<P>
Two former NBA players of Andrew Gaze and Shane Heal paced the
hosts, known as Boomers, to the hard fought victory. The two
guards combined for 43 points to confirm the win over Lithuania,
the bronze winner at the 1996 Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Gaze hit 18 points, including four three pointers, while Heal
led the hosts with a game high 25 points.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks, Australia has defeated European
champions Italy, world champions Yugoslavia and African champions
Angola in the Hong Kong Diamonds Ball tournament.
</P>
<P>
Its 89-64 defeat to the defending champions the United States
was the least margin that the so-called "Dream Team" ever scored
in the warm-up games prior to the Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
