<HEADLINE> Lifter Mutlu Eyes on Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 11 (Xinhua) -- World weightlifting record
holder Halil Mutlu of Turkey said Monday night he is confident to
win the gold medal of the 56kg category at the Sydney Olympic
games.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, I'm confident of taking the gold though I face some
challenges in the competition," Mutlu, gold medal winner at the
1999 world and the European championships this year, told Xinhua
after he finished his training.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old lifter snatched 140-, jerked 170- for a total
of 310-kgs in the training session this evening, all surpassing
his own current world mark -- 132.5 for the snatch, 166.5 for the
jerk and 302.5 for the total.
</P>
<P>
"My form is good. Winning the gold is my hope in Sydney. But
lifters from Bulgaria and China, and maybe some other countries,
are also very strong, I must be careful on the way for the gold,"
Mutlu added.
</P>
<P>
His performance in training well sends threatening information
to his rivals. Chinese headcoach Yang Hanxiong said that if he
could lift the weight in competitions, no one could challenge him
for the gold.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu will fight for goal on September 16, the opening of
weightlifting at the Sydney Convention Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
