<HEADLINE> First Automated Bank in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The first 24-hour self-
service bank in northwest China is now in operation in Yinchuan,
capital of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The local branch of the Bank of China (BOC), one of the four
major commercial banks in China, is the operator of the quick-
serve bank.
</P>
<P>
Banking specialists say that this is BOC's way of introducing
advanced banking technology, offering convenient service and
gaining an edge on its competitors in the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Within minutes, bank customers can complete transactions
involving cash savings and withdrawal, account management, and
financial consulting at the bank at any time, where automatic
teller machines, computer systems for service consulting and other
banking equipment are available, according to BOC officials.
</P>
