<HEADLINE> China to Issue More Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China is to issue 80 billion
yuan worth of treasury bonds on September 15, the Ministry of
Finance announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The T-bonds include 48 billion yuan worth of 3-year bonds and
32 billion yuan worth of 5-year bonds. The annual interest rate of
the 3-year bonds is 2.89 percent, while that for the 5-year bonds
is 3.14 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be sold to individual investors at commercial
banks around the country from September 15 to December 15.
</P>
