<HEADLINE> 1-Trillion-Yuan State-Owned Enterprises Debt Swapped into Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China has swapped more than
one trillion yuan worth of bad debts from state-owned enterprises
into shares held by debt management companies.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with a seminar on capital restructuring of
the financial sector at the on-going China investment and trade
fair in Xiamen, the country's four debt management companies have
already taken over bad debts from 569 state-owned enterprises
around the country.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the debt management companies will sell part
of the shares that they own to overseas investors at an
appropriate date.
</P>
<P>
China began to conduct debt-stake swaps for debt-laden state-
owned enterprises in April 1999 as a major step to turn around the
poor performing enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
