<HEADLINE> Special TV Program for Teachers Airs Tonight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- "Candle Night," a special TV
program to commemorate China's 16th Teachers' Day, will be
broadcast tonight by China Educational Television (CETV).
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the China Charity Federation (CCF), CETV, Phoenix
TV and Hubei TV, the program aims to highlight Chinese teachers'
contributions in nurturing the country's younger generation.
</P>
<P>
In China, teachers are compared to candles, because both share
the characteristics of self-sacrifice.
</P>
<P>
The Candle Project, initiated by CCF in 1998, is also named for
teachers and aims to lessen the burden of teachers in poor rural
schools and improve their professional qualifications.  
