<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Shares Ease on Weak Banking, Tech Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended lower on
Singapore Stock Market Monday, dampened by the selling of banking
and technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index fell 15.44 points, or 0.72
percent, to 2,119.61.
</P>
<P>
Volume was weak at 192.66 million units worth 412.85 million
Singapore dollars (240.03 million U.S. dollars). Decliners
outnumbered gainers by 419 to 73 with 123 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
SingTel led the volume list with a turnover of 11.45 million
units. It was followed by Federal which had 10.9 million shares
done. PacC MLcw00 was the next with 5.7 million counters changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 became the biggest gainer, rising 50 cents to 28.1
Singapore dollars. DBS, SPH and SembLog each gained 30 cents to 21.
7, 28.1 and 10.7 Singapore dollars respectively. SingTel,
SingTel10 and SingTel100 each edged up 8 cents to 2.78, 2.76 and 2.
76 Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
PacCent led the descent of the day, plunging by 130 cents to 20.
7 Singapore dollars. Venture fell 80 cents to 20.5 Singapore
dollars and Creative 50 shed 70 cents to 36.7 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
