<HEADLINE> Xiamen Export Processing Zone Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Xiamen
Export Processing Zone started this morning, bringing the number
of such zones in China to 15.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Haicang Taiwanese Investment Zone of Xiamen, a
port city in southeast China's Fujian province, the new export
processing zone covers an area of 2.4 square kilometers and will
be constructed in two phases.
</P>
<P>
The first phase, covering 1.46 square kilometers in area, is
expected to open to enterprises by the end of 2001.
</P>
<P>
The Haicang Taiwanese Investment Zone, approved by the State
Council in 1989, had attracted more than 140 foreign-funded
enterprises as of July this year, with a total investment of 3.34
billion U.S. dollars. There are also 240 domestic-funded
enterprises operating in the zone, involving an investment of 10.
48 billion yuan (1.26 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The zone signed eight contracts on foreign investment projects
at the ongoing Fourth China Fair for International Investment and
Trade, which opened in Xiamen on September 8. The eight projects
involve a combined contractual foreign investment of 269.45
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In another development from the international fair, China
Export Commodities Network created an online investment and trade
fair system that enables clients to identify the commodities they
need and want on the Net. 
</P>
</TEXT>
