<HEADLINE> State Councilor Meets Japanese Youth Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor
Ismail Amat met today with a Japanese youth delegation led by Sato
Yoshiyasu, former Japanese ambassador to China and vice chairman
of the Japan-China Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
Ismail Amat said that developing a stable Sino-Japanese
relationship is in the interests of the people of the two
countries and helps promote world peace and development. He urged
younger generations of the two countries not to forget the history,
to look forward to the future, to increase dialogue and expand
common acknowledgment while enhancing the awareness of the
importance of developing Sino-Japanese relations so as to involve
themselves in the cause of Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
The 100-member delegation is visiting China under the 1998
program designed to expand exchanges between youth of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Beijing, the delegation will visit Hohhot,
Zhengzhou, Changsha and Shanghai. 
