<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
finished weaker Monday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark S&AMP;P/ASX200 dropped 23.2 points to 3,297.1 while
the All Ordinaries Index lost 24 points to 3,255.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 429.21 million shares valued at 1.298
billion Australian dollars (725.19 million U.S. dollars), with 867
falls, 497 rises and 481 stocks steady.
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight News Corp lost 39 cents to 23.45 Australian
dollars and PBL closed steady at 14.35 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telco giant Telstra ended 4.5 cents weaker at 6.215 Australian
dollars while C&AMP;W Optus dipped 7 cents to 4.3 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks were mostly weaker except Westpac which ended 3.
5 cents stronger at 12.8 Australian dollars. National Australia
Bank fell 6 cents to 25.3 Australian dollars, Commonwealth Bank
dropped 12.9 cents to 26.98 Australian dollars and ANZ eased 3 to
13.12 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The insurance company AMP ended 13.1 cents softer at 17.47
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Resources major Rio Tinto added 60 cents to 27.3 Australian
dollars, but BHP dropped 7 cents to 20.1 Australian dollars and
Woodside lost 35 cents to 13.9 Australian dollars. 
</P>
