<HEADLINE> China to Turn Weaponry Base into Holiday Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- China is planning to transform
a weaponry base in the northwestern province of Shaanxi into the
nation's largest holiday village with national defense as its
theme.
</P>
<P>
The project is among those proposed at the fourth China Fair
for International Investment and Trade, currently being held in
the eastern coastal city of Xiamen, Fujian Province, and has
aroused great interest among the participants, according to
sources with the fair.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500 million yuan (60 million U.S. dollars) will be
needed for turning the No. 051 weaponry base into a tourism base,
which highlights defense technology and a variety of entertainment
related to the military.
</P>
<P>
The project covers an area of 30 square kilometers and is
located some 90 kilometers east of the famous tourist city of Xi'
an.
</P>
<P>
The holiday village will consist of four areas, including
amusement facilities, a defense education center, a hot spring inn
and a base for defense technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
