<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Malaysians Kidnapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Three Malaysians
reported missing from a resort at Pandanan Island near Semporna of
Sabah, East Malaysia, Sunday night were Monday confirmed kidnapped
by an armed group which staged a robbery at the resort.
</P>
<P>
"All three are Malaysians," Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi told reporters here.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah, who is also home minister, said police had informed
him that the armed men might comprise foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The information is based on the Malay dialect used by members
of the group which is similar to the language spoken by people in
the southern Philippines, he said.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said police were still investigating the group
responsible for the kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
The three were reported missing after a band of four men armed
with M-16 rifles robbed Pandanan Semporna Island Resort at
Pandanan Island.
</P>
<P>
Pandanan Island is about 20 nautical miles from Semporna and
not far from Sipadan Island where the Abu Sayyaf group from the
Philippines kidnapped 21 people,including nine Malaysians, on
April 23 and held them hostage in Jolo island in the southern
Philippines for months.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the abduction was again by the Abu Sayyaf armed
group, Abdullah said police were investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
