<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Slightly Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly weaker Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Australian dollar was 55.87 U.S. cents from
55.89 at the local close Friday, 59.44 yen from 58.95 and 64.23
euro cents from 64.44.
</P>
<P>
Governor of the Australian Reserve Bank Ian Macfarlane
reportedly said in a speech at the World Economic Forum in
Melbourne Monday that markets were underestimating the strength of
the Australian economy when valuing the Australian dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar has declined since last November from
around 65 U.S. cents to under 60 U.S. cents at present. 
