<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Cross Chooses Uganda as Center for Relief Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The International Federation
of the Red Cross (IFRC) has chosen Uganda as a coordination center
for relief activities in the Great Lakes Region, The New Vision
newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We chose Uganda as a center for all the regional co-operation
and partnerships among the Great lakes countries, because it has
the best, useful and interesting national society and also the
best volunteering working relationship with the authorities," said
visiting President of the Red Cross Astrid Heiberg.
</P>
<P>
"We have learnt what happened in the Democratic Republic of the
Congo, the food insecurity in Ethiopia and the ethnic conflicts in
Burundi and Rwanda, we know these have had a big impact on Uganda,
causing a danger of a huge wave of refugees in Uganda," Heiberg
said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda has over 220,000 people suffering from food insecurity
in the north, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
