<HEADLINE> U.N. Appeals for 2 Million U.S. Dollars to Ease Uganda's Food Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is
appealing for 2.1 million U.S. dollars from the international
community to support Uganda's efforts to end its current food
shortage, the New Vision daily reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The U.N. appeal for Uganda includes an agricultural component
prepared by the Food Agriculture Organization (FAO) comprising of
five project proposals amounting to 2.1 million dollars," says a
FAO report from Rome.
</P>
<P>
"The project addresses the most urgent needs of the food
insecure population in Uganda," the report said, adding that the
project will enhance the food security of 80,900 affected families
in Kasese and Kabarole districts in western Uganda.
</P>
<P>
In response to the appeal for assistance to Uganda, FAO has
received 230,000 U.S. dollars from the Swedish government for the
provision of essential agricultural inputs to 6,000 drought-
affected farming households in Kasese and Kabarole, according to
Anne Bauer, chief of Special Relief Operations Service in Rome.
</P>
</TEXT>
