<HEADLINE> Nine People Perish in Road Accidents in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed in
two separate road accidents in Kenya on Sunday, local newspapers
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation newspaper reported that five died on the Kiganjo-
Nanyuki road in Laikipia District in central Kenya when a tour van
and a saloon car collided in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the saloon car, whose female driver was among
the dead, had tyre burst, causing it to swerve and collide with
the van.
</P>
<P>
Two occupants in the saloon car died on the spot, while three
others were confirmed dead on arrival at the Nanyuki General
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Both vehicles were at a high speed on the newly-recarpeted road
when the accident occurred, said Cyrus Mutungi, one of the
eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
Another four people, a man and three females, were killed in a
road accident along the Mombassa-Nairobi road near the Athi River,
some 30 kilometers southeastern of the capital Nairobi, the East
African Standard newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
A police officer from the Athi River Police Station at the
crash scene said the driver of a Toyota car traveling from
Mombassa to Nairobi was trying to overtake a tipper truck when
another vehicle heading to Mombassa appeared, and the Toyota car
rammed into the truck's rear, killing all the four inside.
</P>
</TEXT>
