<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Al Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Education Minister Hussein Kamel Bahaeddin said
illiteracy rate in Egypt decreased to 33.4 percent, by 4.2 million
people, in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Students in primary stage have increased by 12 percent, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat is to arrive in Cairo on
Monday on a brief visit to Egypt for talks with President Hosni
Mubarak within the framework of continued coordination between the
two leaders.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will brief Mubarak on his recent meetings on the sideline
of the United Nations Millennium Summit as well as the two-day
Palestinian Central Council meeting which concluded Sunday with a
decision to postpone declaration of statehood.
</P>
<P>
