<DOCNO> XIE20000911.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Host African Assembly on Adult Education Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will host the first
ever Pan African Association for Literacy and Adult Education (
PAALAE) general assembly next year, Times of Zambia newspaper
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement released by the Adult Education
Association of Zambia, the assembly with the theme of "Adult
Education in the New Millennium" will run from May 23 to 26 in
Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
Zambia was nominated by other countries in appreciation of the
great strides the nation had taken in fight against illiteracy in
both urban and rural programs, it said.
</P>
<P>
The PAALAE was set up on April 28 in Dakar, Senegal with a
prime objective to contribute significantly to the 50 percent
improvement of the regional literacy rate by 2015.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's illiteracy rate stands at 60 percent. The majority of
the illiterates are women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
