<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 3 points higher at 2,091 with a slight
turnover of 68.2 million NZ dollars (28.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom, which makes up about a third of the stock market,
gained 7 cents to 645 cents, Independent News 3 to 399 cents,
forestry giant Carter Holt Harvey 2 to 180 cents, and Fletcher
Forests 1 cent to 84 cents.
</P>
<P>
Insurer AMP fell 36 cents to 2,301 cents, Fletcher Energy 13 to
872 cents, New Zealand's largest brewer Lion Nathan 6 to 474 cents,
and discount retailer the Warehouse 5 to 595 cents.
</P>
<P>
Both Fletcher Building and pay television network Sky TV closed
unchanged at 237 and 390 cents respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
