<HEADLINE> Calm Returns to World Economic Forum Summit Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Calm returned outside the
World Economic Forum in Melbourne at noon Monday after earlier
violent confrontations between police and protesters.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Associated Press AAP reported that the most
significant incident was the one in which the car of West
Australian Premier Richard Court was blocked by the protesters for
nearly an hour.
</P>
<P>
Two people were reportedly arrested.
</P>
<P>
Minor casualties were caused in skirmishes. A protester lost
three teeth in the incident blocking Premier Court's car. He was
hit by a mounted police officer with a truncheon and suffered
severe facial injuries.
</P>
<P>
A policeman received crush injuries to his abdomen and chest,
AAP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
