<P>
NEW DELHI, September 11 (Xinhua) -- India welcomed the decision
of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) in
Vienna to increase the crude oil production by 800,000 barrels per
day.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the announcement of the OPEC decision on Sunday,
Indian Petroleum and Natural Gas Minister Ram Naik expressed his
hope that the increase, which is three percent of the present OPEC
production quota, would have "a salutary and lasting effect on
international oil prices."
</P>
<P>
However, according to a statement issued Sunday night, the
minister said New Delhi would have been happier if the increase
was of a larger magnitude considering the already very high prices
and the strong demand in the market.
</P>
<P>
Indian economy, especially aviation and land transports, was
hit hard by the increase of oil prices in the international
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
