<HEADLINE> DPRK Special Envoy Begins Visit to South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A special envoy of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) arrived here Monday
for a four-day visit for talks to further implement the South-
North Joint Declarations signed this June.
</P>
<P>
Kim Yong Sun, a special envoy of DPRK leader Kim Jong Il and
one of his closest confidants, flew into Seoul directly from
Pyongyang Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who is in charge of concrete inter-Korean affairs, will
meet with South Korean Unification Minister Park Jae-kyu Monday
afternoon to discuss inter-Korean issues, especially the
reconnection of the Seoul-Shinuiju Railroad, government officials
said.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to attend a banquet hosted by South Korean
Prime Minister Lee Han-dong Wednesday and meet with President Kim
Dae-jung Thursday before he returns to the DPRK capital.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Kim and his eight-member delegation, will
visit the southern resort island of Cheju, the ancient city of
Kyongju, and Pohang Iron and Steel Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The visit by Kim, who heads the DPRK Asia-Pacific Peace
Committee, shows the inter-Korean relations have reached a
substantive stage for harmony and cooperation, the officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
