<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympics Encounter More Transport Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Trains between Sydney and
Olympic Park were halted on Monday at one of the city's busiest
stations when the Millennium Games is to be opened four days later.
</P>
<P>
However, the problem was solved promptly and the rails were
cleared fairly and quickly without any major conjestion.
</P>
<P>
An Olympic transport spokesman said "these kinds of problem
happen from time to time. We know what to do and we have extra
staff to work on these issues and we have got our response times
down pretty well."
</P>
<P>
The rail system in Sydney has been hit by a series of
derailments and signal failures in the last three months, while
athletes and officials have complained about buses running late or
not turning up. 
</P>
