<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Set up Modern Cyber City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A modern cyber city is to be
set up in the suburbs of Sri Lankan Capital city of Colombo at
Malabe, a senior government official said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a gathering recently at a college, Commerce Minister
Kingsley T. Wickremeratne said that the city will be similar to
India's Silicon Valley in Bangalore, which is the well-known
hitech center.
</P>
<P>
Wickremeratne said it will enable people from all parts of Sri
lanka to gain knowledge and skills to become world class
professionals in the business of information technology and
management.
</P>
<P>
The new campus of the cyber city will train 1,200 persons per
year supplying about 50 percent of Sri Lanka's needs in this area
while private sector institutions of equal excellence will provide
the balance.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Sri Lanka has been pushing for expansion in
information technology. Special tax concessions have been offered
to the private sector for undertaking training in computer
technology. An increasing number of government institutions have
also become involved in information technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
