<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The following are the
highlights of today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin returned to Beijing Sunday
after attending the United Nations Millennium Summit from
September 6 to 8, the biggest gathering of heads of state or
governments in the UN history.
</P>
<P>
When he returned, Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao and Vice
Premier Wu Bangguo, member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee greeted Jiang and his entourage in the Great Hall of the
People.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Zhu Rongji, Sunday, visited a hospital in Urumqi,
capital of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, to comfort those
injured in a Friday evening explosion.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred when a vehicle carrying explosives that
were set to be destroyed was traveling on Xishan Road in the
western suburbs of Urumqi, killing 60 people and injuring more
than 200 others.
</P>
