Guangming Daily
</P>
<P>
 -- East China's Jiangsu Province has recently issued an order
banning underground water extraction, for an unspecified period of
time, in Suzhou, Changzhou and Wuxi,the most developed cities in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the excessive use of underground water in the area
over the past several years has caused serious geological problems,
including the sinking of land.  
