<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 16 Killed in Head-on-Train Collision in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people were
killed and dozens injured when two trains collided head-on on
Sunday at Ketanggang village in Batang, Central Java, Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
A passenger train from Jakarta heading towards Semarang,
Central Java, had collided with a cargo train running from
Surabaya, East Java, at Ketanggang at around 6:30 a.m. local time,
the Jakarta Post daily Monday quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
Police said many passengers were pinned down between the irons
and that up to 17:00 p.m. rescuers could still not take them out.
Victims were taken to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Police are still investigating the cause of the collision, the
most deadly train accident this year.
</P>
<P>
On January 13, 12 people sitting on top of an electric train
plying between Bogor and Sukabumi died and 10 others were injured
after they hit a bridge in Paledang near Bogor, West Java.
</P>
</TEXT>
