to deploy the National Missile Defense(NMD) is "rational".
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao, in a statement
on the matter, said that China has taken note of such a decision
made by President Clinton on September 1, and held that the
decision is rational.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth International Congress of the World Federation of
Public Health Associations (WFPHA) opened in Beijing on September
2, with attendance of over 1,300 participants from 40 countries
and regions. The congress closed on September 6.
</P>
<P>
On September 4, Chinese media reported Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's interview with Mike Wallace, 82-year-old anchor of the "60
Minutes" program of the Columbia Broadcasting System (CBS), in the
seaside resort of Beidaihe, about 300 kilometers east of Beijing,
on August 15. In that interview, Jiang said that as the new
century approaches, it is imperative to "build towards a
constructive strategic partnership" between China and the United
States. Jiang also talked about a wide range of topics with the
American correspondent in the interview.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin left Beijing in the afternoon of
September 4 to attend the United Nations Millennium Summit, which
was held at the United Nations headquarters from September 6 to 8.
Jiang returned to Beijing yesterday by a special plane after
attending the United Nations Millennium Summit.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China (PBOC) announced on September 5 that
it will liberalize the lending rate of foreign currencies starting
from September 21. Major reform measures are also made
simultaneously on the deposit rate of foreign currencies,
according to a circular issued on September 5 by the PBOC, the
central bank.
</P>
<P>
