<HEADLINE> Spaniard Carlos Sainz Wins the Cyprus Rally 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Carlos Sainz,
driving a Ford, managed to win the Cyprus Rally 2000 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sainz and his co-driver Luis Moya lead throughout the three-day
rally, reaching the finish 37.3 ahead of runner up Colin McRae and
his co-driver Nicky Grist, in the other Ford.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Francois Delecour and his co-driver Daniel Grataloup
in their Peugeot finished third just 52.5 behind Mcrae.
</P>
<P>
Briton Richard Burns in a Subaru came in fourth, while world
champion Tommi Makinen, driving a Mitsubishi, was fifth.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturer's prize was given to the Ford team.
</P>
<P>
Of the 52 cars that participated in the Cyprus Rally 2000, 28
managed to finish and complete the 23 tough special stages, mainly
gravel.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Rally is for the first time included in the calender
of the International Automobile Federation's World Championship.
</P>
</TEXT>
