<HEADLINE> Safin Beats Sampras for U.S. Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 10 (Xinhua) -- Russian Marat Safin toppled
four-time champion Pete Sampras by straight sets to win the U.S.
Open men's singles championship for his first Grand Slam title
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Safin defeated Sampras 6-4, 6-3, 6-3 in one
hour and 38 minutes to become the first Russian ever to win the U.
S. Open. 
