<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2030 GMT, September 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami
proposed on Monday to give the Palestinians "functional autonomy"
over the Temple Mount in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Israel Radio, Ben-Ami said this would
give "symbolic expression" to the Palestinians desire for
sovereignty over the area, paving the way for an agreement.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that "there can not be joint sovereignty" over
the holy site. (Israel-Palestine-Sovereignty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran will increase its oil output to 3.84 million
barrels per day as of October 1 in accordance with its new quota
within the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), an
Oil Ministry official said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He told the official IRNA news agency that with OPEC's new
production ceiling up to 26.2 million barrels per day, Iran's share
in the amount would rise to 3.84 million barrels per day from the
current 2.72 million barrels. (Iran-OPEC-Production)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- An Iranian court has sentenced 24 people to one to
five years in prison for taking part in riots and attacks on public
buildings in March in the northwestern city of Khalkhal, a
judiciary official announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 52 people were tried for their involvement in the
riots, which were sparked by a decision by the conservative
Guardians Council (GC) to annul the results of the February 18
Majlis (parliament) elections in the town.
</P>
<P>
But only 24 of them were found guilty of damaging public
properties, and the others were acquitted. (Iran-Riots-Sentences)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami
Monday welcomed the Palestinian decision to postpone the
declaration of statehood, but refused to regard it as a favor that
Israel should pay for in return.
</P>
<P>
Ben-Ami said he did not see any change in Palestinian National
Authority Yasser Arafat's attitude in the peace talks. Arafat wants
an agreement and "their idea to postpone the declaration means they
want to exhaust" the possibility for striking a peace deal, he told
Xinhua at a press conference in the Foreign Ministry. (Israel-FM-
Palestine) 
</P>
</TEXT>
