<HEADLINE> Russia to Boost Software Cooperation With India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government decided
to set up a commission to expand Russian-Indian cooperation in
developing software products, Russian Deputy Prime Minister Ilya
Klebanov told the press here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Klebanov said this decision was taken Monday during his talks
with representatives of the Confederation of Indian Industrialists
at the White House, the Russian government headquarters, ahead of
Russian President Vladimir Putin's visit to India in the beginning
of October.
</P>
<P>
The commission will be attached to the Russian-Indian
intergovernmental commission, said Klebanov. Russian-Indian
cooperation in this field would be mutually advantageous, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Russian and Indian experts also discussed
future joint pharmaceutical, machine-building and aircraft-
building projects, Klebanov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
